  <!--hinh giao dien-->
  <section class="hero-section text-center py-5" style="background-image: url(/public/images/eggcoffee.png);">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="display-4 text-white">Egg Coffee</h1>
    </div>
  </section>
  <main>
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <div class="row mt-4">
        <div class="col-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-6">
          <div>
            <h2>Description</h2>
            <p>
              Making Vietnamese egg coffee (Cà Phê Trứng) is an indulgent treat, blending the bold flavor of coffee with a sweet, creamy, custard-like foam.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-6">
          <dl>
            <div class="container-fluid">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-12 col-sm-6">
                  <dt>
                    <span>Ingredients</span>
                  </dt>
                  <dd>
                    <ol>
                      <li>
                        Coffee: 2 tablespoons of strong Vietnamese coffee or any robust dark roast coffee (brewed)
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Egg yolk: 1 large, fresh egg yolk
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Sweetened condensed milk: 2 tablespoons
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Sugar (optional): 1 teaspoon (if you like extra sweetness)
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Vanilla extract (optional): 1-2 drops
                      </li>
                    </ol>
                  </dd>
                </div>
                <div class="col-12 col-sm-6">
                  <dt>
                    <span>Equipments</span>
                  </dt>
                  <dd>
                    <ol>
                      <li>
                        A small whisk or hand mixer (a fork can also work)
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        A glass or ceramic mug
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        A bowl for whisking
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        A Vietnamese coffee filter (phin) or any method for brewing strong coffee
                      </li>
                    </ol>
                  </dd>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="py-3">
      <h3>1. Brew the coffee</h3>
      <ul class="m-0">
        <li>
          Prepare a small cup of strong Vietnamese coffee using a phin filter or another method (e.g., espresso machine, French press).
        </li>
        <li>
          Keep the brewed coffee hot while preparing the egg mixture.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section class="py-3">
      <h3>2. Separate the egg yolk</h3>
      <ul class="m-0">
        <li>
          Carefully crack the egg and separate the yolk from the white. Discard or save the white for another recipe.
        </li>
        <li>
          Place the yolk in a mixing bowl.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section class="py-3">
      <h3>3. Make the egg cream</h3>
      <ul class="m-0">
        <li>
          Add the sweetened condensed milk to the yolk. If you want, add a teaspoon of sugar for extra sweetness and a drop or two of vanilla extract for flavor.
        </li>
        <li>
          Whisk the mixture thoroughly using a small whisk, hand mixer, or fork. Continue until the mixture is pale, thick, and frothy (about 5 minutes).
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section class="py-3">
      <h3>4. Assemble the egg coffee</h3>
      <ul class="m-0">
        <li>
          Pour the brewed coffee into a serving cup.
        </li>
        <li>
          Gently spoon the whipped egg mixture on top of the coffee. You can carefully spread it with a spoon for an even layer.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section class="py-3">
      <h3>5. Serve and enjoy</h3>
      <ul class="m-0">
        <li>
          Serve immediately while hot. Traditionally, the cup is placed in a small bowl of hot water to keep it warm.
        </li>
        <li>
          To drink, either sip through the foam or stir it lightly into the coffee for a creamy, rich experience.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>

